:INFO
Google Reviews for a Trades Business
A steady stream of genuine Google reviews is the single best local marketing asset for a plumber, electrician, landscaper, or cleaner. Build a simple system for asking, responding, and monitoring.

:COUNTER.half
50 Reviews
Threshold where Google ranking effects become visible
|
:COUNTER.half
24 Hours
Target response time for every new review

:PATH
Ask for Reviews
Ask in person right after the job while the customer is happy. Send a follow-up text two hours later with your direct review link. Include the link on every invoice and thank-you card.

:PATH
Respond to Every Review
Thank positive reviewers by name and mention the specific job. Respond to negative reviews calmly, apologize for the experience, and offer to make it right offline. Never argue publicly.

:PATH
Monitor Your Reputation
Set up a Google Alert for your business name. Check Google Business Profile weekly. Use a tool like Birdeye or Podium if you want automated review requests by SMS.

:CHECKLIST
Review Strategy Checklist
[ ] Claim and verify your Google Business Profile if not done
[ ] Generate your direct review link from Google Business Profile
[ ] Create a short URL or QR code for the review link
[ ] Print the QR code on invoice footers and thank-you cards
[ ] Write a review request SMS template for post-job follow-up
[ ] Set a goal of 5 new reviews per month
[ ] Respond to every review within 24 hours

:NOTE
Never offer incentives in exchange for reviews. Google prohibits it and it can get your listing suspended. Genuine reviews from real customers are the only sustainable approach.

:LINK
https://business.google.com
Google Business Profile Manager
